  <h3 id="the-perfect-mile">7. "The Perfect Mile" by Neal Bascomb</h3>
  <p>
    This biography tells the story of the quest to break the four-minute mile
    barrier in the 1950s. Bascomb's writing is filled with suspense and drama,
    making for a truly exhilarating read.
  </p>
  <ProductsContainer products={1} />
</TextSection>
